Use the standard library
This is how to parse_nested_parens of paren_string:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that groups is split of paren_string and " "
   Remember that g is 0
   Do this groups's length times:
      Remember that group is item g in groups
      Remember that max_depth is 0
      Remember that current_depth is 0
      Remember that i is 0
      Do this group's length times:
         Remember that c is item i in group
         When c is 40, then:
            Increase current_depth
            When current_depth is more than max_depth, then:
               Remember that max_depth is current_depth
            End when
         End when
         When c is 41, then:
            Decrease current_depth
         End when
         Increase i
      End do
      Add result to max_depth
      Increase g
   End do
   The answer is result
